MongoDB Shell

Constant

This query uses the following pipeline stages:

- [$search](pipe.$search) to query the collection. The query:

  - Uses the following `compound` operator clauses:

    - `filter` clause with the [range](range-ref) operator to
      search for movies between the years `2013` to `2015`.

    - `should` clause with the [text](text-ref) operator to query
      for the term `snow` in the `title` field and alter the
      `score` with the `constant` option. The `constant` option
      replaces all score results for the search term with `5`.

  - Specifies the [highlights](highlight-ref) option to return snippets of text
    from the `title` field that match the query. The snippets contain
    matching text specified with `type: 'hit'`, and adjacent text
    specified with `type: 'text'`.

- [$limit](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/limit) stage to limit the output to
  `10` results.

- [$project](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/project) stage to:

  - Exclude all fields except `title` and `year`

  - Add a `score` field

```json
db.movies.aggregate([
  {
    "$search": {
      "index": "default",
      "compound": {
        "filter": [{
          "range": {
            "path": "year",
            "gte": 2013,
            "lte": 2015
          }
        }],
        "should": [{
          "text": {
            "query": "snow",
            "path": "title",
            "score": {"constant": {"value": 5}}
          }
        }]
      },
      "highlight": {
        "path": "title"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "$limit": 10
  },
  {
    "$project": {
      "_id": 0,
      "title": 1,
      "year": 1,
      "score": { "$meta": "searchScore" },
      "highlights": { "$meta": "searchHighlights" }
    }
  }
])
```

